{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, KTO performed slightly better, indicating that the choice of fine-tuning method is an important parameter for future research.",
    "We see that fine-tuning can enhance performance with increased training, but the improvements observed were minimal.",
    "Fine-tuning tends to adjust the model's responses to fit a desired style but is insufficient to significantly alter the weights for the binary classification of network attacks.",
    "Pre-trained natural language models, which are trained on extensive natural language corpora, may not be capable of recognising the subtle patterns that indicate malicious NetFlows.",
    "They are more adept at generating appropriate responses to natural language queries without any further deep understanding.Fine-tuning LLMs for detecting malicious NetFlows is unnecessary; instead, transformer-based models can be trained directly on entire datasets."
  ]
}